ces/TrophyIcons_111_b.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":1,"_index":10},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.sqoMqRJEnOb37RkT","dataType":"compendium","name":"Quell Magic","img":"icons/magic/perception/orb-crystal-ball-scrying-blue.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":9,"_index":11},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.RE7FYClEdmstA90o","dataType":"compendium","name":"Stances Known (Mystic)","img":"All%20Icons/Resources/TrophyIcons_111_b.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":1,"_index":12},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.Tu4KVOnNAQkPVwc1","dataType":"compendium","name":"Withstand Spell","img":"icons/magic/perception/orb-crystal-ball-scrying-blue.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":5,"_index":13},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.VevcYahrWvwZqJdW","dataType":"compendium","name":"Mystic Artifice","img":"icons/magic/perception/orb-crystal-ball-scrying-blue.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":4,"_index":14}]},"tag":"","useCustomTag":false,"armorProf":{"value":[],"custom":""},"weaponProf":{"value":[],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":[],"custom":""},"flags":{"boolean":[],"dictionary":[]},"scriptCalls":[],"classType":"base","level":1,"hd":8,"hp":8,"bab":"med","skillsPerLevel":4,"savingThrows":{"fort":{"value":"low"},"ref":{"value":"low"},"will":{"value":"high"}},"fc":{"hp":{"value":0},"skill":{"value":0},"alt":{"value":0,"notes":""}},"classSkills":{"acr":true,"apr":false,"art":false,"blf":false,"clm":false,"crf":true,"dip":false,"dev":false,"dis":false,"esc":false,"fly":false,"han":false,"hea":false,"int":true,"kar":true,"kdu":true,"ken":true,"kge":true,"khi":true,"klo":true,"kna":true,"kno":true,"kpl":true,"kre":true,"lin":false,"lor":false,"per":true,"prf":true,"pro":true,"rid":false,"sen":true,"slt":false,"spl":true,"ste":true,"sur":false,"swm":false,"umd":true},"customHD":"","identifiedName":"Mystic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"pGtrBsyWNme2G1e0":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.0rlsvFZjVdhwZLxA"}},"_id":"1xjCND9uFx6UvtzJ"}
{"name":"Warlord","type":"class","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-human.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Dynamos on the field of combat, warlords walk the line of victory and ruin through their determination to achieve glory. Where some may talk tactics, the warlord dives in. Where some may fight in strategic units, the warlord shines alone as an inspirational beacon on the field of combat; to be a warlord is to be a lord of war.</p>\n<p>Adventures: Warlords adventure for many reasons, but one reason that will always be prominent is the desire to test their skill against the world&rsquo;s most dangerous opponents, to show their strength to themselves and to the world. Others may do this for profit, others for fun, others for revenge, but it is always certain that a warlord seeks the glory and honor only a battle well-fought can bring.</p>\n<p>Characteristics: Brash arrogance and an irrepressible nature are hallmarks of the warlord. A devil-may-care warrior, many warlords are as fearless as they are fierce, and they both love life and live their lives to the fullest. Hedonists in some extreme cases, the warlord is drawn to combat as a moth to the flame. Alignment: Any. Warlords can come from any and all ethical backgrounds, though they do tend more towards a chaotic&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Alignment\">alignment</a>. Lawfully aligned warlords are rarer, and tend to compose their impulses through strict discipline.</p>\n<p>Religion: While not overly religious, some warlords follow gods of war and battle with temperaments similar to their own.</p>\n<p>Background: Warlords come from families with strong warrior traditions, from barbaric tribes and from academies that produce the strongest warriors. One thing that sets them apart is their reckless nature and the inspirational presence they possess.</p>\n<p>Races:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/human\">Humans</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/half-elf\">half-elves</a>&nbsp;are prominent warlord races due to both possessing an impetuous nature.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/Half-orc\">Half-orcs</a>&nbsp;become very fearsome warlords in their own right, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/dwarf\">dwarves</a>&nbsp;are known for their ferocity when defending their homes.</p>\n<p>Other Classes: Warlords get on well with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/fighter\">fighters</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/ranger\">rangers</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/barbarian\">barbarians</a>&nbsp;as their martial nature makes them amicable, but&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/paladin\">paladins</a>&nbsp;and warders tend to chafe under their recklessness. Wizards and especially&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/bard\">bards</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/sorcerer\">sorcerers</a>&nbsp;get on quite well with them, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/cleric\">clerics</a>&nbsp;find them to be tolerable.</p>\n<p>Role: Striker. As a very aggressive class, the warlord seeks to bring martial power to the field in the form of overwhelming force and ferocity. Additionally, warlords make excellent leaders, as they provide some passive benefits from their class features as well as active benefits from discipline choices and their gambits.</p>\n<p>Abilities:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Charisma</a>&nbsp;are incredibly important to a warlord, as without&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a>&nbsp;the warlord is weaker in combat and without&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Charisma</a>&nbsp;many of his abilities will not function, as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Charisma</a>&nbsp;is the warlord&rsquo;s primary initiation attribute.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Constitution-Con-\">Constitution</a>&nbsp;is important for vital&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Hit-Points\">hit points</a>.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Intelligence</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;take up the bottom of importance, for both skill points and defense (or ranged combat).</p>\n<p>Hit Die: d10</p>\n<p>Starting Wealth and Age: As&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/fighter\">fighter</a>.</p>\n<h2>Class Skills</h2>\n<p>The warlord&rsquo;s class skills (and the key ability for each skill) are:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/acrobatics\">Acrobatics</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dex</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/climb\">Climb</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Str</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/craft\">Craft</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/diplomacy\">Diplomacy</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Cha</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/handle-animal\">Handle Animal</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Cha</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/intimidate\">Intimidate</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Cha</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a>&nbsp;(engineering) (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a>&nbsp;(history) (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a>&nbsp;(martial) (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/perception\">Perception</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/profession\">Profession</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/ride\">Ride</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dex</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/sense-motive\">Sense Motive</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/survival\">Survival</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wis</a>),&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/swim\">Swim</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Str</a>).</p>\n<p>Skill Ranks per Level: 4 +&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Int</a>&nbsp;modifier</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"links":{"children":[],"classAssociations":[{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.ds7QyDK1E3B1x0Bi","dataType":"compendium","name":"Battle Prowess","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-human.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":5,"_index":0},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.NTUJHL4SHAlMsXHw","dataType":"compendium","name":"Bonus Feat","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-human.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":1,"_index":1},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.6hiLyJRX2LKRKvpQ","dataType":"compendium","name":"Dual Boost","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-human.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":6,"_index":2},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.uXOwEUzusP70euxl","dataType":"compendium","name":"Dual Stance","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-human.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":20,"_index":3},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.kp5ZFjsRhFcnEgkd","dataType":"compendium","name":"Dual Tactical Presence","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-human.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":11,"_index":4},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.HRAGzwl69EwIsyEE","dataType":"compendium","name":"Force of Personality","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-human.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":3,"_index":5},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.mJqpmQbcyMj3q43e","dataType":"compendium","name":"Improved Warleader","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-human.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":13,"_index":6},{"id":"world.path-of-war-class-abilities.EB20cOtJKnTgybXw","dataType":"compendium","name":"Maneuvers (Warlord)","img":"All%20Icons/Resources/TrophyIcons_111_b.webp","hiddenLinks":{},"level":1,"_index":7},{"id":"world.path-o